line_1: That mild associate Psyche now deserts,
line_2: The vile magician all his art exerts,

line_1: Which she encourag'd to their best Deserts:
line_2: Next to the Poor are those of Noble Arts,

line_1: 'Roose you sae weel for your deserts,
line_2: 'Shall bauld L*****K, the king o' hearts,

line_1: 'Roose you sae weel for your deserts,
line_2: ' Tho' mankind were a pack o' cartes,

line_1: 'Roose you sae weel for your deserts,
line_2: 'Yet ye'll neglect to shaw your parts

line_1: Still ask, but ne'er consult their own deserts,
line_2: And measure by their interest, not their parts.
On all alike his tongue exerts;
